Oner mechanic I know drills a hole dead center of the emblem and puts in
a stainless screw and dremels off the slot.  To ever remove the emblem,
you dremel off the head.  If it is reachable from the rear, I suppose a
bolt cound be used.
George Lyle wrote:
 
 Having lost an emblem to some punk gang-banger type, I would suggest
 nuts.  You can get flanged rubber washers at hardware stores to fill
up> the holes.

